<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.7864290>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Nuclear genome tree of selected Moncina: Phlebodes relatives. See Fig. 4 for notations. Some genera are labeled at their clades. Taxa discussed in the text are shown in different colors: Cantha (purple, with species transferred from Phlebodes labeled in dark green), Duroca (violet, with Duroca caraca, comb. nov. and Duroca lenta, stat. nov. labeled in aquamarine and brown, respectively). Green arrows point from the clade of the genus where a species was previous placed to the clade of the species that is being transferred between genera." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/7864290/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

